The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 i-flex to pay 100% dividend

 New Delhi, Aug. 13 (PTI): Global information technology solution provider i-flex Solutions Ltd has decided to pay a 100 per cent dividend to its shareholders.

 At its sixteenth annual general meeting held in the city today, the board of directors took a decision to this effect, the Mumbai-based company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 Besides approving the audited balance sheet as on March 31, 2005, the shareholders meeting also resolved to issue and allot 80,000 warrants to IBM Global Services India Pvt Ltd, the company release said.

 The company further adopted a resolution authorising the board of directors to issue and allot warrants or options up to 0.5 per cent of fully diluted equity to GE Capital Mauritius Equity Investment, a designated affiliate of General Electric Capital Corpo- ration.




